{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019xWjuCbsSxLvS8qB2NFuJb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# ray/worker_recovery\n2\t# Fix the ray-worker deployment whose startup command has an invalid flag causing crash loops\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  The Ray head is running, but the worker pods are crash looping.\n6\t  The worker startup command includes an invalid flag, so workers never join\n7\t  the cluster.\n8\t\n9\t  Your task: fix the ray-worker deployment so the worker command starts\n10\t  successfully and connects to ray-head:6379.\n11\t\n12\t  Requirements:\n13\t  - Remove the invalid flag from the worker command.\n14\t  - Ensure the worker deployment reaches 2 ready replicas.\n15\t\n16\t  Success criteria: ray-worker has 2 ready replicas and Ray reports 3 live nodes.\n17\t\n18\tnamespace_contract:\n19\t  required_roles: []\n20\t\n21\tmetrics:\n22\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n23\t\n24\tpreconditionUnits:\n25\t  - name: ray_env_ready\n26\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n27\t    probe:\n28\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n29\t        timeout_sec: 10\n30\t    apply:\n31\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n32\t        sleep: 0\n33\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n34\t        sleep: 1\n35\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n36\t        sleep: 2\n37\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\"\n38\t        sleep: 2\n39\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n40\t        sleep: 1\n41\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-client.yaml\"\n42\t        sleep: 1\n43\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=60s\"\n44\t        sleep: 1\n45\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- ray start --address=ray-head:6379\"\n46\t        sleep: 2\n47\t    verify:\n48\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n49\t        timeout_sec: 10\n50\t\n51\toracle:\n52\t  verify:\n53\t    commands:\n54\t      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/worker_recovery/oracle/oracle.py\"\n55\t        timeout_sec: 180\n56\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"818b031e-800e-4d25-8175-91dde3e5c442","uuid":"f812357b-15c6-436b-8250-72766b9a759f","timestamp":"2026-06-16T08:32:42.437Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/cases/ray/worker_recovery/test.yaml","content":"# ray/worker_recovery\n# Fix the ray-worker deployment whose startup command has an invalid flag causing crash loops\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray head is running, but the worker pods are crash looping.\n  The worker startup command includes an invalid flag, so workers never join\n  the cluster.\n\n  Your task: fix the ray-worker deployment so the worker command starts\n  successfully and connects to ray-head:6379.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Remove the invalid flag from the worker command.\n  - Ensure the worker deployment reaches 2 ready replicas.\n\n  Success criteria: ray-worker has 2 ready replicas and Ray reports 3 live nodes.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray ap