{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TDmfPDEqUxfjS5NAjQ7Fu8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# ray/adversarial/scale_down_workers\n2\t#\n3\t# Scales the ray-worker Deployment down to a wrong (lower) replica count while\n4\t# the agent is working. This simulates an automation job or operator error that\n5\t# fights the agent's scale-up task. The cluster appears to have fewer workers\n6\t# than intended, causing resource shortfalls for pending jobs. The agent must\n7\t# detect the regressed worker count and restore the target replica count.\n8\t#\n9\t# Targets the literal `ray` namespace used by all Ray cases.\n10\t#\n11\t# Deploy: scale ray-worker down to wrong_replicas.\n12\t# Lift:   if the agent has not already scaled back up, restore to restore_replicas.\n13\t\n14\tparams:\n15\t  namespace:\n16\t    default: ray\n17\t    description: Namespace the Ray cluster runs in.\n18\t  deployment_name:\n19\t    default: ray-worker\n20\t    description: Name of the Ray worker Deployment the adversary scales down.\n21\t  wrong_replicas:\n22\t    default: \"1\"\n23\t    description: Worker replica count the adversary shrinks to (the injected fault).\n24\t  restore_replicas:\n25\t    default: \"3\"\n26\t    description: Healthy worker replica count restored on lift if the agent did not fix it.\n27\t\n28\tdeploy:\n29\t  on_probe_fail: error\n30\t  probe:\n31\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\"\n32\t      timeout_sec: 10\n33\t  apply:\n34\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} scale deployment {{params.deployment_name}} --replicas={{params.wrong_replicas}}\"\n35\t      timeout_sec: 20\n36\t  verify:\n37\t    - command: >-\n38\t        /bin/sh -c \"test \\\"$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\n39\t        -o jsonpath={.spec.replicas})\\\" = '{{params.wrong_replicas}}'\"\n40\t      timeout_sec: 10\n41\t\n42\tlift:\n43\t  on_probe_fail: skip\n44\t  probe:\n45\t    - command: >-\n46\t        /bin/sh -c \"test \\\"$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\n47\t        -o jsonpath={.spec.replicas})\\\" = '{{params.wrong_replicas}}'\"\n48\t      timeout_sec: 10\n49\t  apply:\n50\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} scale deployment {{params.deployment_name}} --replicas={{params.restore_replicas}}\"\n51\t      timeout_sec: 20\n52\t  verify:\n53\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\"\n54\t      timeout_sec: 10\n55\t\n56\tprompt_hints:\n57\t  deploy: |\n58\t    Note: an external process may be changing cluster state during this task.\n59\t    Verify the live worker replica count against the target before assuming the\n60\t    cluster is correctly sized.\n61\t  active: |\n62\t    Reminder: the worker replica count may have been changed by an external actor\n63\t    earlier in this workflow. Re-check before concluding the task is complete.\n64\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"818b031e-800e-4d25-8175-91dde3e5c442","uuid":"7c50988b-b7a6-4d62-ae27-aab2e7888a28","timestamp":"2026-06-16T08:33:00.823Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/adversaries/ray/scale_down_workers/scenario.yaml","content":"# ray/adversarial/scale_down_workers\n#\n# Scales the ray-worker Deployment down to a wrong (lower) replica count while\n# the agent is working. This simulates an automation job or operator error that\n# fights the agent's scale-up task. The cluster appears to have fewer workers\n# than intended, causing resource shortfalls for pending jobs. The agent must\n# detect the regressed worker count and restore the target replica count.\n#\n# Targets the literal `ray` namespace used by all Ray cases.\n#\n# Deploy: scale ray-worker down to wrong_replicas.\n# Lift:   if the agent has not already scaled back up, restore to restore_replicas.\n\nparams:\n  namespace:\n    default: ray\n    description: Namespace the Ray cluster runs in.\n  deployment_name:\n    default: ray-worker\n    description: Name of the Ray worker Deployment the adversary scales down.\n  wrong_replicas:\n    default: \"1\"\n    description: Worker replica count the adversary shrinks to (the injected fault).\n  restore_replicas:\n    default: \"3\"\n    description: Healthy worker replica count restored on lift if the agent did not fix it.\n\ndeploy:\n  on_probe_fail: error\n  probe:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n  apply:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} scale deployment {{params.deployment_name}} --replicas={{params.wrong_replicas}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c \"test \\\"$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\n        -o jsonpath={.spec.replicas})\\\" = '{{params.wrong_replicas}}'\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n\nlift:\n  on_probe_fail: skip\n  probe:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c \"test \\\"$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\n        -o jsonpath={.spec.replicas})\\\" = '{{params.wrong_replicas}}'\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n  apply:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} scale deployment {{params.deployment_name}} --replicas={{params.restore_replicas}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get deployment {{params.deployment_name}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n\nprompt_hints:\n  deploy: |\n    Note: an external process may be changing cluster state during this task.\n    Verify the live worker replica count against the target before assuming the\n    cluster is correctly sized.\n  active: |\n    Reminder: the worker replica count may have been changed by an external actor\n    earlier in this workflow. Re-check before concluding the task is complete.\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
